Edison International (EIX) , owner of
Californiaâ€™s largest electric utility, idled its Sunrise Power
Project in the state for planned work.  The 590-megawatt plant was shut at 3:15 p.m. local time
yesterday, the California Independent System Operator said in a
 report . It had been generating 400 megawatts a day earlier, a
previous  report  showed.  The plant, north of Los Angeles in Kern County, is owned by
Edison and  Chevron Corp. (CVX)   One megawatt can power about 800 typical U.S. homes.  To contact the reporter on this story:
